===Etymology===
{{unk|en}};<ref>T.F. Hoad, ''Concise Dictionary of English Etymology'', {{ISBN|978-0-19-283098-2}}; headword ''penguin''</ref> first attested in the 16th century in reference to the [[auk]] of the Northern hemisphere; the word was later applied to the superficially similar birds of the Southern hemisphere (as was {{m|en|woggin}}). Possibly from {{der|en|cy|pen||head}} and {{m|cy|gwyn||white}}, or from {{der|en|la|pinguis||fat}}. See [[Citations:penguin|citations]] and {{w|Penguin#Etymology|the Wikipedia page}}.

